# Cursor Rules — JHC Project Database Frontend

## Core Tech Stack
- Use React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui + Lucide
- All UI components should follow shadcn/ui composition patterns

## Components & TypeScript
- Use functional components with named exports
- Example: `export function ProjectCard() { ... }`
- Define `ComponentNameProps` interface above each component
- Avoid `any`; use union types for enums (e.g., `'In Progress' | 'Testing' | 'Completed'`)
- Place all domain types in `src/types/` (e.g., `project.ts`)
- Import types using `import type { ... }`

## Styling & UI
- Use Tailwind utility classes only (no inline styles except dynamic values)
- Follow a dark theme using slate-based backgrounds:
  - `bg-slate-950` (app)
  - `bg-slate-900` (cards)
  - `text-slate-100/400/500`
- Use design tokens / class utilities whenever available (e.g., shadcn theme tokens)
- Avoid hardcoded slate colors in new components
- Use `ImageWithFallback` from `src/figma/ImageWithFallback.tsx` for all images, always providing an alt attribute
- Use Lucide icons, imported individually (e.g. `import { Calendar } from "lucide-react"`)
- Default sizes: `w-4 h-4` / `w-5 h-5`

## Structure & Imports
- Use this folder structure:
  - `src/components/` → project components
  - `src/ui/` → shadcn/ui components
  - `src/types/` → all interfaces/types
  - `src/ui/utils.ts` → utility functions (e.g., `cn` for className merging)
  - `src/figma/` → ImageWithFallback component
- Follow this import order:
  1. React
  2. External libs
  3. shadcn/ui components (`src/ui/`)
  4. Project components (`src/components/`)
  5. Types (`src/types/`)
  6. Utils (`src/ui/utils.ts`)

## Code Quality & Performance
- Use `useMemo` and `useCallback` only when needed — i.e., expensive computations or when memoized children require stable references
- Keep components small and single-purpose
- Split components >200 lines; abstract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Handle missing/empty/null data safely
- Use optional chaining (`project?.id`) and nullish coalescing (`value ?? fallback`)

## UX, Modals, & Accessibility
- Dialogs must use shadcn/ui's `<Dialog>` structure with proper focus management and keyboard accessibility
- For fade/opacity transitions, do NOT unmount the element
- Render it always, toggle visibility with Tailwind classes (`opacity-0 opacity-100 pointer-events-none`)

